Endpoints

/achievements

GET /achievements

Gets a list of all known achievements.

    • Response

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<Achievement>
get /achievements Gets a list of all known achievements

/broadcasts

GET /broadcasts/current

Returns the latest or ongoing broadcast from the current user.

    • Response

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Broadcast

404 Not Found

Returned if no broadcast is found.

GET /broadcasts/{broadcastId}

Returns information about the requested broadcast.

    • Request
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • broadcastId:  UUID

    The ID of the broadcast to retrieve.

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Broadcast

404 Not Found

Returned if the broadcast is not found.

GET /broadcasts/{broadcastId}/manifest.{type}

This endpoint is identical to /channels/{id}/manifest.{format}. See that for more information.

    • Request

URI Parameters

  • broadcastId:  UUID

    The ID of the broadcast to retrieve.

  • type:  string

    The manifest format to retrieve.

get /broadcasts/current Returns the latest or ongoing broadcast from the current user
get /broadcasts/{broadcastId} Returns information about the requested broadcast
get /broadcasts/{broadcastId}/manifest.{type} This endpoint is identical to `/channels/{id}/manifest

/channels

GET /channels

As of June 10th, 2017, this endpoint will no longer include offline channels.

A paginated search for online channels.

This endpoint is rate-limited with the channel-search bucket.
    • Request
    • Response

Query Parameters

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=50≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • q:  string

    The search string to be used.

  • scope:  string (all,names)

    Specifies what properties to search in, note that all and names combined.

200 OK

Headers

  • x-rate-limit:  uint

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-remaining:  uint

    How many requests until you meet the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-reset:  UnixTimestampMillis

    When this rate limit bucket expires.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<Channel>
    • Item properties:
      • thumbnail:  Resource
      • user:  User
      • type:  GameType

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

Gets a single channel.

This endpoint is rate-limited with the channel-read bucket.

    The ID or token of the channel.

200 OK

Headers

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-remaining:  uint

    How many requests until you meet the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-reset:  UnixTimestampMillis

    When this rate limit bucket expires.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: ExpandedChannel

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

GET /channels/{channelIdOrToken}/details

Attempts to get channel details, including private ones. Please note that this will not explicitly fail but instead omit private properties if the user does not have the appropriate permission scopes to read them.

  • The channel:streamKey permission is required for the streamKey property to be included.
  • The channel:details permission is required for the numSubscribers property to be included.
    • Request
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • channelIdOrToken:  string ∪ uint

    The ID or token of the channel.

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: ExpandedChannel
    • streamKey:  string

      The users stream key.

    • numSubscribers:  uint

      The current amount of subscribers the channel has.

    • maxConcurrentSubscribers:  uint

      The maximum amount of concurrent subscribers.

    • totalUniqueSubscribers:  uint

      The total amount of unique subscribers the user has had.

PUT /channels/{channelId}

This method is deprecated. Use `patch` instead.
    • Request

URI Parameters

  • channelId:  uint

    The ID of the channel.

PATCH /channels/{channelId}

Updates a channel, responds with the updated channel.

Secured by OAuth 2.0 Scopes: 
channel:update
This endpoint is rate-limited with the channel-write bucket.
    • Request
    • Security
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • channelId:  uint

    The ID of the channel.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Channel

200 OK

Headers

  • x-rate-limit:  uint

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-remaining:  uint

    How many requests until you meet the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-reset:  UnixTimestampMillis

    When this rate limit bucket expires.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Channel

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

channel:update

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

GET /channels/{channelId}/analytics/viewers

This method is deprecated. Use `/channel/{id}/analytics/tsdb` instead.

GET /channels/{channelId}/follow

Paginated listing of the channel's followers.

This endpoint is rate-limited with the channel-read bucket.
    • Request
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • channelId:  uint

    The ID of the channel.

Query Parameters

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=25≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • x-rate-limit:  uint

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-remaining:  uint

    How many requests until you meet the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-reset:  UnixTimestampMillis

    When this rate limit bucket expires.

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<UserWithChannel>

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

GET /channels/{channelId}/users

Gets all users with roles assigned in the channel. Including Subscribers if you have the channels:details:self permission for this user.

    • Request
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • channelId:  uint

    The ID of the channel.

Query Parameters

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=50≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<UserWithGroups>

get /channels A paginated search for online channels
get /channels/{channelIdOrToken} Gets a single channel
get /channels/{channelIdOrToken}/details Attempts to get channel details, including private ones
put /channels/{channelId}
patch /channels/{channelId} Updates a channel, responds with the updated channel
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/viewers Fetches the viewer count over time in a given interval, limited to the last 24 hours
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/viewers Displays viewer counts over time for a channel
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/viewersMetrics Displays information about individual viewers of a channel
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/streamSessions Displays information about when the channel started and stopped streaming, and what they steamed
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/streamHosts Displays when other channels hosted this channel
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/subscriptions Displays when users subscribed to this channel and subscriber number changes over time
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/followers Displays when users followed to this channel and follower number changes over time
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/gameRanksGlobal Returns a list of game views, shares, and the number of streams over the time interval across the platform, grouped per game type
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/subRevenue Returns a summary of revenue earned from subscriptions over the time perio
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/cpm Returns payments awarded via synthetic advertisement impressions
get /channels/{channelId}/analytics/tsdb/viewerSessionCount Returns counts of unique sessions over the period
post /channels/{channelId}/badge Sets the thumbnail for this channel
get /channels/{channelId}/follow Paginated listing of the channel's followers
put /channels/{channelId}/follow
post /channels/{channelId}/follow Follows the channel as a user, whose id is supplied in the request body
delete /channels/{channelId}/follow Un-follows the channel as a user, whose id is supplied in query parameter
get /channels/{channelId}/emoticons Retrieves a sprite sheet and coordinates of this channel's emoticons
patch /channels/{channelId}/emoticons Changes the channel's emoticons
get /channels/{channelId}/hostee Redirects to the channel that is being hosted, if this channel is actively hosting
put /channels/{channelId}/hostee Sets the hosted channel
delete /channels/{channelId}/hostee Stops hosting another channel
get /channels/{channelId}/hostee/layout Returns the layout used in this hosting session
patch /channels/{channelId}/hostee/layout Applies an update to the hosting session layout
get /channels/{channelId}/hosters Gets a list of channels hosting this channel
get /channels/{channelId}/manifest.light2 Gets a stream light2 manifest
get /channels/{channelId}/manifest.m3u8 Gets a stream m3u8 manifest
get /channels/{channelId}/manifest.ftl Gets a stream FTL manifest
get /channels/{channelId}/preferences Reads the channels preferences
post /channels/{channelId}/preferences Sets the channels preferences
get /channels/{channelId}/related Finds related channels
delete /channels/{channelId}/streamKey Resets this channel's stream key
get /channels/{channelId}/relationship Gets the relationship of the channel to a user
post /channels/{channelId}/thumbnail Sets the thumbnail of the channel
get /channels/{channelId}/users Gets all users with roles assigned in the channel
get /channels/{channelId}/users/{role} Lists all users assigned a certain role in the channel, like "mod" or "subscriber"
patch /channels/{channelId}/users/{userId} Updates a user's roles on this channel
get /channels/{channelId}/discord Returns Discord settings for the channel
put /channels/{channelId}/discord Updates Discord settings on the channel
get /channels/{channelId}/discord/channels Lists all voice and text channels in the Discord chat
get /channels/{channelId}/discord/roles Lists all roles available on a channel
get /channels/{channelId}/discord/invite Checks if the user can be invited to the channel's Discord server
post /channels/{channelId}/discord/invite Attempts to create an invite to the Discord Server
get /channels/{channelId}/recordings Returns a list of video recordings owned by the channel
post /channels/{channelId}/transcodes/unlock Unlocks transcodes for the channel
get /channels/{channelId}/confetti Returns the confetti the user has created for their channel
get /channels/{channelId}/banner Returns the banner image the user has selected for their channel
post /channels/{channelId}/banner Adds a banner url to the channel
delete /channels/{channelId}/banner Deletes channel banner
get /channels/{channelId}/broadcast Returns the latest or ongoing broadcast from the channel

/chats

GET /chats/{channelId}

Prepares the user to join a chat channel. It returns the channel's chatroom settings, available chat servers, and an authentication key that the user (if authenticated) should use to authenticate with the chat servers over websockets.

If you wish to connect to chat as an authenticated user, you must have the chat:connect permission.

This endpoint is rate-limited with the chats bucket.
    • Request
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • channelId:  uint

    The ID of the channel you wish to chat in.

200 OK

Headers

  • x-rate-limit:  uint

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-remaining:  uint

    How many requests until you meet the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-reset:  UnixTimestampMillis

    When this rate limit bucket expires.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • endpoints:  Array<string>

      List of chat server websocket urls.

    • authkey:  string

      The auth key required to join a channel's chatroom.

    • roles:  Array<Role>

      List of roles he user will have once joined.

    • permissions:  Array<string>

      List of permissions the user will have once joined.

    • isLoadShed:  boolean

      Whether the channel is in load shedding mode.

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

GET /chats/{channelId}/joinIfNotBigEvent

During big events, chat enters a special mode and frontend clients connect lazily. This endpoint will either return a 409 Conflict code if the channel is a big event, or return the same response code as /chats/{id}.

Generally, using /chats/{id} for building client integrations is sufficient.

This endpoint is rate-limited with the chats bucket.
    • Request
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • channelId:  uint

    The ID of the channel you wish to chat in.

200 OK

See /chats/{id} for an example of a response.

Headers

  • x-rate-limit:  uint

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-remaining:  uint

    How many requests until you meet the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-reset:  UnixTimestampMillis

    When this rate limit bucket expires.

409 Conflict

Returned if the channel is in big event mode.

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

GET /chats/{channelId}/friends

Gets a list of friends for a user currently active in this channel's chatroom.

Secured by OAuth 2.0 Scopes: 
user:details
This endpoint is rate-limited with the channel-read bucket.
    • Request
    • Security
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • channelId:  uint

    The ID of the channel you wish to chat in.

Query Parameters

  • user:  uint

    The user to find the friends for.

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=50≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

  • x-rate-limit:  uint

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-remaining:  uint

    How many requests until you meet the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-reset:  UnixTimestampMillis

    When this rate limit bucket expires.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<User>

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

user:details

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

/clips

GET /clips/broadcasts/{broadcastId}/canClip

Checks if a clip can be created on a given broadcast.

Secured by OAuth 2.0 Scopes: 
channel:clip:create
    • Request
    • Security
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • broadcastId:  string

    ID of the broadcast

200 OK

The clip can be created.

400 Bad Request

The request is invalid for the reason indicated in the response body.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: ClipError

403 Forbidden

The user does not have permission to create clip.

404 Not Found

The broadcast is not found.

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

channel:clip:create

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

      Default costream layout to use when this invite is accepted.

    • inviteeIds:  Array<uint>?

      The user IDs to be invited to the costream.

    • inviteeXUIDs:  Array<uint>?

      The XUIDs to be invited to the costream.

    • inviterId:  uint?

      The user ID doing the inviting. Defaults to the requesting user.

204 No Content

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

channel:costream

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

/delve

GET /delve/home

The delve API is the entry point one-stop-shop for showing Mixer homescreen content across devices. It is accessible at GET /api/v1/delve. Calling clients SHOULD pass the Mixer userId as a query string parameter, if the user is authenticated. This is used to personalize responses. If the call with the userId fails with a 5xx status code, the caller SHOULD retry the request without the userId parameter. This allows us to still serve the homepage in the event of intermitted or catastrophic failure, as the common public/anonymous response will be cached. The caller MAY also provide a hydrate parameter, set to true or false, indicating whether they want response content to be pre-fetched when possible.

The response contains a list of content rows. Each row contains a type, which dictates which logic is used to display that row. Clients MUST gracefully ignore the row entry if they do not have the logic needed to display it.

The client is required to pass a permission check if a userId is provided.

Secured by OAuth 2.0 Scopes: 
delve:view
    • Request
    • Security
    • Response

Query Parameters

  • userId:  number?

    The user ID to delve for, if any.

  • hydrate:  [boolean=true]

    Whether to seed the API response with results

  • audience:  string?

    Comma-delimited list of permitted maturity values for channels returned in the delve. Channels whose maturity setting is not in the list won't be returned for most hydrations.

    Example: 

    family,teen

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • rows:  Array<DelveError | DelveCarousel | DelveGames | DelveChannels>
      • Item type: DelveError ∪ DelveCarousel ∪ DelveGames ∪ DelveChannels
    • mixPlayFilters:  Array<DelveMixPlayFilters>
      • Item type: DelveMixPlayFilters
    • background:  DelveBackground

      Configuration for the background to display.

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

Secured by OAuth Secret

Requires that you have an OAuth client with a secret token, and calls against this endpoint will be made in the context of your application, rather than a particular user. OAuth clients without secret tokens will not be able to call endpoints secured using this scheme.

    • Security
    • Response

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<Webhook>

OAuth Secret Authentication

Requires that you have an OAuth client with a secret token, and calls against this endpoint will be made in the context of your application, rather than a particular user. OAuth clients without secret tokens will not be able to call endpoints secured using this scheme.

Headers

  • Client-ID:  string

    Your OAuth application's client ID.

    Example: 

    da400f1a81d7efc477920b5d686e95be6f92c88af09c2342

    • pattern: 
      [0-9a-f]{48}
  • Authorization:  string

    Contains your OAuth application's secret token in the form "Secret mylongtokenhere"

    Example: 

    Secret c51ff3c4e44e7be32be2f639b28e3569f1775f8530b95a5d972ace2cb9310ab8

    • pattern: 
      ^Secret [0-9a-f]{64}$

GET /interactive/games

Retrieves a paginated list of published interactive games.

    • Request
    • Response

Query Parameters

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=50≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<InteractiveGameListing>

interactive:manage
    • Request
    • Security
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • game:  uint

    The unique ID of the game.

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<User>

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

interactive:manage

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

/jwt

POST /jwt/authorize

Generates a JWT Grant to be used in requests. These tokens can be used in requests. A useful benefit of using a JWT Grant is that no CSRF token is needed for requests. JWT Grants are generally only valid for a few hours at a time and should thus not be stored on disk as authorization method, instead each time you start making requests you should hit this enpoint to get a new JWT. (NOT on every request) Since JWT's are not encrypted, but signed you can inspect the remaining time the token is valid by checking the exp field of the JWT data.

    • Response

204 No Content

Provides grant when authenticated and not returning in body.

Headers

  • X-JWT:  string

    JWT Grant that can be used in the Authorization for requests.

401 Unauthorized

When not authenticated this will return an error.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • statusCode:  uint

      The error code (401).

    • error:  string

      A one word error reason (Unauthorized)

    • message:  string

      A human readable error description.

post /jwt/authorize Generates a JWT Grant to be used in requests

POST /notifications/{notificationId}/shareSub

Shares a sub anniversary notification, sending a chat message in the channel that the anniversary is with. Such a notification may only be shared once and must be shared within five days of when it was sent.

Secured by OAuth 2.0 Scopes: 
user:notification
    • Request
    • Security
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • notificationId:  uint

    The ID of the notification.

204 No Content

400 Bad Request

Sent if the notification is the wrong type, if it was already sent, or if the notification is too old to share.

Sent if the notification was not found.

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

POST /oauth/token

Retrieves an OAuth token. For more information see our OAuth Page!

    • Request
    • Response

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • grant_type:  string (refresh_token,authorization_code)
    • refresh_token:  string?

      Only required when grant_type is refresh_token

    • client_id:  string

      The OAuth client id.

    • client_secret:  string?

      The OAuth client secret, only required if the OAuth client in use has one.

    • code:  string?

      The authorization code received from the /authorize endpoint. Not required for token refreshing.

    • redirect_uri:  string?

      The OAuth redirect uri. Must be identical to the one used with the /authorize endpoint. Not required for token refreshing.

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • access_token:  string

      The access token.

    • token_type:  string

      Always "Bearer".

    • expires_in:  uint

      The lifetime in seconds of the access token.

    • refresh_token:  string

      The refresh token, valid for one year.

POST /oauth/token/introspect

Implements token introspection, listing the token scopes and various other information about the grant.

    • Request
    • Response

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • token:  string

      The access or refresh token to look up.

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • active:  boolean

      True if the token is valid and usable, false otherwise. When false, no other values will be returned.

    • scope:  string

      Space-delimited list of scopes the token is granted.

    • client_id:  string

      The client ID associated with the token.

    • username:  string

      Username of the user to whom this token is granted.

    • token_type:  string

      The type of the token, "access_token" or "refresh_token"

    • exp:  number

      Second timestamp when the token expired.

    • sub:  number

      User ID of the user to whom this token belongs.

POST /oauth/shortcode

Initializes the "shortcode" auth flow. The endpoint takes a client_id, client_secret, and scope similarly to the initial authorization request. It returns a short, six-digit code to be displayed to the user to link their account in addition to a longer "handle" that can be used for polling its status in POST /oauth/code/{handle}.

    • Request
    • Response

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • client_id:  string

      The OAuth client ID.

    • client_secret:  string?

      The OAuth client secret, only required if the OAuth client in use has one.

    • scope:  string

      List of permissions separated by whitespace.

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • code:  string

      The short six-digit code to be displayed to the user.

    • handle:  string

      A longer, random string to use while checking the code's status in POST /oauth/code

    • expires_in:  uint

      The amount of time until the code expires, in seconds.

GET /oauth/shortcode/check/{handle}

Checks the status of a previously issued code and, after it's been activated, returns an OAuth authorization code to be passed to GET /oauth/token to exchange it for an access and refresh token. Once again, the client ID and secret (if any) are required.

    • Request
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • handle:  string

    The code handle as returned in POST /oauth/code

200 OK

Sent once after authorization succeeds

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • code:  string

      The OAuth code to exchange for access and refresh tokens.

204 No Content

Send if the code is still valid but the user hasn't granted it yet.

403 Forbidden

Sent if the user denied the user denied the requested permission.

404 Not Found

Sent if the code handle is not found or expired, or if the client_id mismatches that of a discovered token.

GET /oauth/twitter/check

Used to get the user to authenticate with the provider. If they're authed, it'll redirect to /oauth/check/confirm. If they deny authentication, it directs to /oauth/check/deny.

POST /oauth/twitter/check

Same as get

POST /oauth/twitter/link

Links an OAuth account to the user's current account.

DELETE /oauth/twitter/link

Removes a service previously linked to an account.

POST /oauth/twitter/login

Attempts to login using the provider oauth. Like normal login, except that it returns a 404 if the provider account is not yet linked to any Mixer account.

    • Response

200 OK

GET /oauth/twitter/profile

Shows the profile of the currently authenticated user on the provider.

POST /oauth/twitter/register

Attempts to register using the provider's oauth. It takes a post request body like the normal register endpoint, but fills in all properties by default.

/recordings

GET /recordings

Lists all available VOD recordings.

    • Request
    • Response

Query Parameters

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=50≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<Recording>

    Filter for share subject.

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=50≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<ExpandedShare>

Creates a new subscription.

Secured by OAuth 2.0 Scopes:

    • Request
    • Security
    • Response

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: object
    • user:  uint

      The ID of the user.

    • group:  Role

      The group name.

    • terms:  [1≤uint=1]

      The amount of terms this subscription should run for.

    • channel:  uint?

      The channel id, only if the subscription is for a channel.

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Invoice

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

subscription:create

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

channel:update

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

/types

GET /types

Lists available channel types. Alternatively provides auto completion capabilities when supplying the "query" parameter.

    • Request
    • Response

Query Parameters

  • query:  string

    A substring of a type to search for. When specified and page is unspecified GameTypeSimple results will be returned instead and the search attempts to find around 15 entries it may return more or less. All other lister parameters will be ignored.

    Otherwise the query will be used for a wildcard search on the name field and ordered by likeness to the query.

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=50≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: GameType[] ∪ GameTypeSimple[]

    • Request
    • Response

Query Parameters

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

user:update

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

GET /users/{user}/follows

Paginates list of the channels the channel user is following.

This endpoint is rate-limited with the channel-read bucket.
    • Request
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • user:  uint

    The ID of the user

Query Parameters

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=25≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • x-rate-limit:  uint

    How many requests you can make before hitting the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-remaining:  uint

    How many requests until you meet the limit.

  • x-ratelimit-reset:  UnixTimestampMillis

    When this rate limit bucket expires.

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<ChannelAdvanced>

429 Too Many Requests

API rate limit exceeded.

    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<ExpandedRedeemable>

GET /users/{user}/resources

List of all resources the user owns or has access to.

Secured by OAuth 2.0 Scopes: 
resource:find
    • Request

    • Response

  • user:  uint

    The ID of the user

200 OK

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<Resource>

OAuth 2.0 Authentication

Scopes

Requires the following OAuth Scopes:

resource:find

Headers

  • Authorization:  string

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Prefixed by "Bearer". Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter. Alternatively can be used to send an xbl authorization header.

    Example: 

    `Bearer ttlpmeOT5QuNbdN2c2IvHz8KY0VAwhrorc1o8BshdyxUGSoYLU1dpz8B5MaP28lR` or `XBL3.0 x=userHash;xtoken`

401 Unauthorized

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Mixer revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

403 Forbidden

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here. Can also indicate a missing permission for the action attempted.

GET /users/{user}/subscriptions

Retrieves a list of subscriptions for this user.

Secured by OAuth 2.0 Scopes: 
subscription:view
    • Request
    • Security
    • Response

URI Parameters

  • user:  uint

    The ID of the user

Query Parameters

  • order:  string?

    Allows specifying an ordering over one or more columns.

    Example: 

    someColumn:ASC,anotherColumn:DESC

  • page:  uint?

    The index of the page.

  • limit:  [1≤integer=50≤100]

    Amount of items per page.

  • where:  string?

    Allows specifying a where clause with 3 operations:

    • eq: The value is equal to.
    • ne: The value is not equal.
    • Deprecated: neq: The value is not equal. Use ne instead.
    • in: The value is in the list of semicolon seperated values.
    • notIn: The value is not in the list of semicolon separated values.
    • between: The value is between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • notBetween: The value is not between two semicolon separated numeric values.
    • gt: The value is greater than.
    • gte: The value is greater than or equal to.
    • lt: The value is smaller than.
    • lte: The value is smaller than or equal to.

    Note: Previously we used . to delimit columns, operations, and values. This usage is now deprecated, we recommend using colons : instead, as shown in the example.

    Example: 

    someColumn:eq:myValue,someOtherColumn:ne:myOtherValue,foo:in:a;b;c,bar:between:1;10

  • fields:  string?

    Allows specifying a projection. Additionally, you can exclude certain properties by prefixing them with a -.

    Example: 

    someColumn,anotherColumn,aThirdColumn

  • noCount:  boolean?

    If specified, the x-total-count header will be omitted. Please use this if you do not require the total count.

200 OK

Headers

  • link:  string

    RFC5988 links, which contains links to first, next, prev and last page.

    Example: 

    <some/path?page=0>; rel="first",<some/path?page=1>; rel="next",<some/path?page=0>; rel="prev",<some/path?page=4>; rel="last"

  • x-total-count:  uint

    Describes the total amount of items.

Body

  • Media Type: application/json
  • Data Type: Array<SubscriptionWithGroup>

Models & Types

Achievement

Achievements are earnt by users and have various requirements.

  • slug:  string

    Unique string identifier for the achievement.

    • maxLength: 100
  • name:  string

    Human readable name for the achievement.

  • description:  string

    The description of the achievement, usually describes requirements for earning it.

  • sparks:  uint

    The number of sparks awarded to a user when this achievement is earnt.

AchievementEarning extends TimeStamped

An AchievementEarning represents a user's progress towards an achievement.

  • id:  uint

    The unique ID of the earning.

  • earned:  boolean

    Indicates whether the achievement was earned.

  • progress:  number≤1

    Unit interval indicating the progress.

  • achievement:  string

    The name of the achievement.

  • user:  uint

    The ID of the user this earning belongs to.

  • Achievement:  Achievement

    Contains the details of the earnt achievement.

Announcement

Announcements are triggered by Mixer staff and inform users of important information and news on Mixer.

  • message:  string

    Message to display in the toast / desktop notification.

  • timeout:  number?

    How long the message should appear for, defaults to 10 seconds.

  • sound:  string (whoosh,chimes,click,dudup,harp,heads-up,here-you-go,hi,incoming,ping,ring,urgent,powers)?

    Any sound that should be played with the announcement, like "whoosh", defaults to null.

  • level:  string (error,warning,info,success)?

    Level of the toast to display, defaults to success.

  • confetti:  number ∪ boolean

    ID of confetti to display, or true to use the default.

Broadcast

A broadcast represents a single broadcast from a Channel.

  • id:  UUID

    Unique ID for this broadcast.

  • channelId:  uint

    ID of the Channel this broadcast belongs to.

  • online:  boolean

    True if this broadcast is online and in progress.

  • isTestStream:  boolean

    True if this broadcast is running in test stream mode.

  • startedAt:  IsoDate

    The date that this broadcast started at.

CPMAnalytic extends ChannelAnalytic

A metric showing the impressions and payout for a period.

  • impressions:  uint

    The number of unique ad impressions.

  • payout:  number

    The amount of money awarded from the impressions, in cents.

Channel extends TimeStamped

A single channel within Mixer. Each channel is owned by a user, and a channel can be broadcasted to.

  • id:  uint

    The unique ID of the channel.

  • userId:  uint

    The ID of the user owning the channel.

  • token:  string

    The name and url of the channel.

  • online:  boolean

    Indicates if the channel is streaming.

  • featured:  boolean

    True if featureLevel is > 0.

  • featureLevel:  -1≤integer

    The featured level for this channel. Its value controls the position and order of channels in the featured carousel.

  • partnered:  boolean

    Indicates if the channel is partnered.

  • transcodingProfileId:  uint?

    The id of the transcoding profile.

  • suspended:  boolean

    Indicates if the channel is suspended.

  • name:  string

    The title of the channel.

  • audience:  string (family,teen,18+)

    The target audience of the channel.

  • viewersTotal:  uint

    Amount of unique viewers that ever viewed this channel.

  • viewersCurrent:  uint

    Amount of current viewers.

  • numFollowers:  uint

    Amount of followers.

  • description:  string

    The description of the channel, can contain HTML.

  • typeId:  uint?

    The ID of the game type.

  • interactive:  boolean

    Indicates if that channel is interactive.

  • interactiveGameId:  uint?

    The ID of the interactive game used.

  • ftl:  uint

    The ftl stream id.

  • hasVod:  boolean

    Indicates if the channel has vod saved.

  • languageId:  string?

    ISO 639 language id.

  • coverId:  uint?

    The ID of the cover resource.

  • thumbnailId:  uint?

    The resource ID of the thumbnail.

  • badgeId:  uint

    The resource ID of the subscriber badge.

  • bannerUrl:  string

    The URL of the the banner image.

  • hosteeId:  uint

    The ID of the hostee channel.

  • hasTranscodes:  boolean

    Indicates if the channel has transcodes enabled.

  • vodsEnabled:  boolean

    Indicates if the channel has vod recording enabled.

  • costreamId:  UUID?

    The costream that the channel is in, if any.

Augmented regular channel with additional data.

  • type:  GameType?

    A nested type showing information about this channel's currently selected type.

  • user:  UserWithGroups

    This channel's owner

ChannelAnalytic

A base analytics type for channel based analytical metrics.

  • channel:  uint

    The channel.

  • time:  IsoDate

    Timestamp for when this metric was recorded.

ChannelFeatures

A list of channel features.

ChannelPreferences

Channel preferences are a list of options and attributes which control behaviour for the channel. Please see each property for more details.

  • sharetext:  string?

    The text used when sharing the stream. The template parameter %URL% will be replaced with the channel's URL. The template parameter %USER% will be replaced with the channel's name.

  • channel:links:allowed:  boolean?

    Specifies whether links are allowed in the chat.

  • channel:links:clickable:  boolean?

    Specifies whether links are clickable in the chat.

  • channel:slowchat:  number?

    Interval required between each chat message.

  • channel:notify:directPurchaseMessage:  string?

    The message to be sent when a user completes a direct purchase on the channel. The template parameter %USER% will be replaced with the name of the user who completed direct purchase. The template parameter %CHANNEL% will be replaced with the name of the channel. The template parameter %GAMETITLE% will be replaced with the name of the game purchased.

  • channel:notify:subscribemessage:  string?

    The message to be sent when a user subscribes to the channel. The template parameter %USER% will be replaced with the subscriber's name.

  • channel:notify:subscribe:  boolean?

    Indicates whether a notification should be shown upon subscription.

  • channel:notify:followmessage:  string?

    The message to be sent when a user follows the channel. The template parameter "%USER%" will be replaced with the follower's name.

  • channel:notify:follow:  boolean?

    Indicates whether a notification should be shown upon follow.

  • channel:notify:hostedBy:  string?

    The message to be sent when a user hosts the channel. The template parameter "%USER%" will be replaced with the hoster's name.

  • channel:notify:hosting:  string?

    The message to be sent when the channel hosts another. The template parameter "%USER%" will be replaced with the hostee's name.

  • channel:partner:submail:  string?

    The text to be added to the subscription email.

  • channel:player:muteOwn:  boolean?

    Indicates whether to mute when the streamer opens his own stream.

  • channel:tweet:enabled:  boolean?

    Indicates whether the tweet button should be shown.

  • channel:tweet:body:  string?

    The message to be used when a user tweets about the channel. The template parameter %URL% will be replaced with the share url.

  • hypezone:allow:  boolean

    Indicates if the channel allows HypeZone to host it.

  • hosting:allow:  boolean

    Indicates if the channel allows other channels to host it.

  • costream:allow:  boolean

    Allows other streamers to join you in a costream.

  • channel:offline:autoplayVod:  boolean?

    When a user visits the channel while the channel is offline, the most recent VOD will be automatically played if this preference is enabled.

Confetti

Represents a confetti cannon configuration. Each channel can have is own customized confetti. The confetti cannon is triggered on subscription or direct purchase events on a channel.

  • id:  uint

    The Confetti's ID.

  • channelId:  uint?

    The owner of the Confetti; this channel can edit it.

  • settings:  object

    The settings configure the confetti. Most options are customizable math expressions parsed with expr-eval.

    • count:  string

      Expression to be evaluated to determine the number of generated confetti particles. The window height and width will be passed into the expression. The number of confetti particles will be capped based on the device profile, however. For example: "count": "35 * width / 100".

    • particles:  Array<object>

      Array of particle configurations.

      • Item properties:
        • probability:  number

          Weighted probability that a generated confetti particle will be this particle. Weighting is done based on the sum all probabilities.

        • velocity:  string

          Expression to be evaluated to determine the vertical velocity, in pixels per millisecond, of the particle. It's called with the window width and height. For example: "velocity": "height / 1000 / 4".

        • zdepth:  string

          Expression to be evaluated to determine the "depth" of the particle, which will be used to scale its size and velocity to achieve a pseudo-3d effect. It's called with the window width and height. For example: "zdepth": "1 + random(3)".

        • wiggleMagnitude:  string

          Expression to determine the magnitude of the wave, in pixels, that each particle follows on its horizontal axis as it floats down. It's called with the window width and height. For example: "wiggleMagnitude": "15 + random(10)".

        • wigglePeriod:  string

          Expression to determine the period of the wave, in milliseconds, that each particle follows on its horizontal axis as it floats down. It's called with the window width and height. For example: "wigglePeriod": "1000 + random(500)".

        • lifetime:  string

          Expression to determine how long each particle lives for, in milliseconds, before being destroyed. It's called with the window width and height. For example: "lifetime": "1200 + random(2000)".

        • fader:  string

          Expression called continuously to determine the opacity. It's called a lifetime values, which starts at zero and goes to one as the time passes, and should return an opacity value in the range from zero to one. For example: "fader": "1 - lifetime^3".

        • draw:  ConfettiCircle ∪ ConfettiRectangle ∪ ConfettiImage

          Describes the confetti graphic to be drawn.

ConfettiCircle

A definition for a circle within a Confetti configuration.

  • shape:  string

    Must be set to circle.

  • size:  string

    Expression to determine the diameter of the confetti circle in pixels. For example: "size": "4 + random(2)"

  • flipPeriod:  string

    Expression to determine the length of time the circle takes to do a vertical, pseudo-3d spin around the x axis. For example: "flipPeriod": "500 + random(1000)"

  • colors:  Array<object>

    A color configuration for this item.

    • Item properties:
      • probability:  number

        Weighted probability that a generated confetti particle will be this color. Weighting is done based on the sum all probabilities.

      • r:  string

        Expression used to generate the red color component, should return a value between 0 and 255 inclusive.

      • g:  string

        Expression used to generate the red color component, should return a value between 0 and 255 inclusive.

      • b:  string

        Expression used to generate the red color component, should return a value between 0 and 255 inclusive.

ConfettiImage

A definition for an image within a Confetti configuration.

  • shape:  string

    Must be set to image.

  • scale:  string

    Expression to determine the scale of the image. For example: "scale": "0.5 + random(1)"

  • spinPeriod:  string

    Expression to determine the length of time the images takes to do a full spin around the z axis. For example: "spinPeriod": "1000 + random(1000)"

  • data:  string

    Base-64 encoded image data. This will usually be a long string that starts with data:image/png;base64,. Make sure to minify the image before inserting it here to prevent exceeding size limits.

ConfettiRectangle

A definition for a rectangle within a Confetti configuration.

  • shape:  string

    Must be set to rectangle.

  • width:  string

    Expression to determine the width of the confetti circle in pixels. For example: "size": "8 + random(2)"

  • height:  string

    Expression to determine the height of the confetti circle in pixels. For example: "size": "4 + random(1)"

  • flipPeriod:  string

    Expression to determine the length of time the circle takes to do a vertical, pseudo-3d spin around the x axis. For example: "flipPeriod": "500 + random(1000)"

  • colors:  Array<object>

    A color configuration for this item.

    • Item properties:
      • probability:  number

        Weighted probability that a generated confetti particle will be this color. Weighting is done based on the sum all probabilities.

      • r:  string

        Expression used to generate the red color component, should return a value between 0 and 255 inclusive.

      • g:  string

        Expression used to generate the red color component, should return a value between 0 and 255 inclusive.

      • b:  string

        Expression used to generate the red color component, should return a value between 0 and 255 inclusive.

Costream

A co-stream is a set of channels grouped together and displayed on Mixer together.

  • channels:  Array<object>

    The members of the costream. The first member in this array is the "host" and has some special permissions regarding kicking other members and changing layout.

    • Item properties:
      • id:  uint

        The unique ID of the channel.

      • userId:  uint

        The ID of the user owning the channel.

      • token:  string

        The name and url of the channel.

  • startedAt:  IsoDate

    The time the costream started.

  • capacity:  uint

    The total number of people who may join this costream.

  • layout:  PlayerLayout

    The layout of a costream, configurable by the host or inviter.

DelveBackground

Dictates what background to display on the homepage.

  • fullWidthSrc:  string

    URL for the background to display full-width, used on mobile and on screens narrower than the max content width.

  • leftSrc:  string?

    Optional left-flanking background for use on screens larger than the max content width.

  • rightSrc:  string?

      • id:  uint
      • type:  string (SUBS,FOLLOWERS)

        Describes what group of people are given this role.

      • roleId:  string
      • gracePeriod:  uint

        Number of days subscribers have until they're kicked from the server if their subscription expires. It defaults to 14 days and may be set to null to disable kicking. Violence is never the answer.

Ingest

An ingest definition. Ingests are used by streaming software to send video to Mixer.

Example:

{
   "name": "US: Dallas, TX",
   "host": "ingest-dal.mixer.com",
   "pingTest": "ingest-dal.mixer.com",
   "protocols": [
      {
         "type": "ftl"
      },
      {
         "type": "rtmp"
      }
   ]
}
  • name:  string

    The name and location of the ingest.

  • host:  string

    Url of the host.

  • pingTest:  string

    A websocket address that is used for ping tests.

  • protocols:  Array<object>

    List of supported protocols

    • Item properties:
      • type:  string (ftl,rtmp)

        The protocol name.

  • notifySubscriber:  Array<string>

    A list of transports subscriber notifications will be sent over.

  • liveOnByDefault:  Array<string>

    A list of notification transport wentlive notifications are sent on by default.

  • lastRead:  IsoDate

    The time the user last read their notifications.

  • health:  object

    Controls the health notification settings for this user.

    • eat:  number≤72

      Interval, in hours, to show eating notifications.

    • stretch:  number≤72

      Interval, in hours, to show stretching notifications.

  • liveNotifications:  Array<object>

    A list of channels and transports registered on which we'll send wentlive emails.

    • Item properties:
      • channelId:  uint ∪ string

        May be "*", which will toggle on the associated transport for all channels the user follows.

      • kind:  string
  • transports:  Array<object>

    Controls the transports used to deliver notifications to this user.

    • Item type: object

PartnershipApp extends TimeStamped

Contains details about a particular partnership application.

  • status:  string (applied,accepted,denied)

    The state of this application, which may be one of:

    • applied - The Application has been submitted and is under review by the Team.
    • accepted - The Application has been accepted.
    • denied - The Application has been denied.
  • reapplies:  IsoDate?

    The date of the next possible application, only set if status is denied. If the value is null while status is denied, the channel is banned from re-applying.

  • reason:  string?

    The reason of the denial, only set if status is denied.

PartnershipCriterion extends TimeStamped

A criterion that a channel must meet in order to apply for partnership.

  • id:  number

    The ID of the criterion that was tested.

  • name:  string

    The friendly name of the criterion that was tested.

  • description:  string

    The description of the criterion that was tested.

  • type:  string

    The type of evaluation to perform.

  • comparison:  string (LT,LTEQ,EQ,GTEQ,GT)

    The type of comparison to perform between the target and actual, which may be one of:

    • LT - The target is less than the actual.
    • LTEQ - The target is less than or equal to the actual.
    • EQ - The target is equal to the actual.
    • GTEQ - The target is greater than or equal to the actual.
    • GT - The target is greater than the actual.
  • target:  number

    The target number that the channel must meet to be considered valid.

  • isEnabled:  boolean

    Whether or not the criterion is enabled. Disabled critera will not affect evaluation.

PartnershipCriterionResult

The result of evaluating a partnership criterion.

  • criterionId:  number

    The ID of the criterion that was tested.

  • type:  string

    The type of evaluation to perform.

  • comparison:  string (LT,LTEQ,EQ,GTEQ,GT)

    The type of comparison to perform between the target and actual, which may be one of:

    • LT - The target is less than the actual.
    • LTEQ - The target is less than or equal to the actual.
    • EQ - The target is equal to the actual.
    • GTEQ - The target is greater than or equal to the actual.
    • GT - The target is greater than the actual.
  • target:  number

    The target number that the channel must meet to be considered valid.

  • actual:  number

    The actual result of the evaluation.

  • succeeded:  boolean

    Whether or not the channel passed the criterion.

  • followers:  PartnershipCriterionResult

    Each property is a mapping from an app or game to what permissions it has to a user's progression storage. Each property's name is an OAuth clientId or an Xbox game title ID.

ProgressionEvent

A type that contains information about a notification event to be sent for progression storage changes.

  • id:  UUID

    The unique ID of this event.

    The name of this event.

  • type:  string (unspecified,unlock,valueUpdate)

  • continuationToken:  string?

    The token to use to retrieve the next page of results, if there are more results.

  • results:  Array<ProgressionEvent>

    The list of progression project events.

ProgressionGameAccess

Available rights in comma delimited string:

  • none - no access, should not be used with other rights.
  • readFromAudience - allows a game or app to read values from viewers' storage.
  • writeToAudience - allows a game or app to write to viewers' storage.
  • readFromPlayer - allows a game or app to read project storage of the authenticated user.
  • writeToPlayer - allows a game or app to write to project storage of the authenticated user.
  • deletePlayerStorage - allows a game or app to delete project storage of the authenticated user, if the project is not published.

ProgressionLocalizedNotification

A type that contains information about an operation to run against a player or channel viewers.

  • awardMessage:  string?

    Notification to be sent to the viewer if the operation results in a value change.

  • awardMessageDetails:  string?

    Additional details to be shown if the notificatrion is clicked.

  • id:  UUID

    Guid of this event, matches with notificationEventId of ProgressOperation

  • language:  string

    The two digit language code of the language the event should be rendered in

  • name:  string

    The non-localized friendly name of the event.

  • type:  string (unspecified,unlock,valueUpdate)

    The type of the event.

  • maxDisplayLengthInMilliseconds:  uint

    Maximum time that the awardMessages string will be shown. Typically this is on the firect of these events recieved.

  • minDisplayLengthInMilliseconds:  uint

    Minimum time that the awardMessages string will be shown to the viewer.

ProgressionOperation

A type that contains information about an operation to run against a player or channel viewers.

  • amount:  number?

    The value to modify a current value by. Required for all operations except notify.

  • awardMessage:  string?

    Notification to be sent to the viewer if the operation results in a value change.

  • awardMessageDetails:  string?

    Additional details to be shown if the notificatrion is clicked.

  • maxVal:  number

    Maximum value restriction. The operation will not run if the result will violate this constraint.

  • minVal:  number

    Minimum value restriction. The operation will not run if the result will violate this constraint.

  • notificationEventId:  UUID

    Unique ID of this operation. Can be used to send events without a notification or for localized award messages.

  • op:  ProgressionOperationType

    The operation to perform on the current value.

  • sessionIds:  Array<UUID>

    a list of viewer session IDs to restrict this operation to executing for. Can be correlated with a Mixplay interactive participant's sessionID.

  • stat:  string

    The name of the value to operate on. Required for all operations except notify.

  • timeRestriction:  string (daily,monthly,weekly)

    Restricts this operation from running if the value has already been modified within the time interval.

ProgressionOperationError

A type that contains information a viewer session and failed operation.

  • sessionId:  UUID

    The session IS of the user that this failure occurred for. Can be correlated with a Mixplay interactive participant's sessionID

  • error:  string

    The information on the failure that occurred.

ProgressionOperationErrors

A type that contains information about failures in a partial success operation.

  • errors:  Array<ProgressionOperationError>

    A list of users that had failures and what those failures were.

ProgressionOperationType

Available operations are:

  • inc - Increment, an addition operation.
  • dec - Decrement, a subtraction operations.
  • and - A bitwise AND operartion.
  • or - A bitwise OR operation.
  • xor - A bitwise XOR operation.
  • set - A direct overwrite of any existing value.
  • notify - Forces a notification without a corresponding value modification.

ProgressionOperations

A type that contains information about progression operations to run against a player or channel viewers.

  • operations:  Array<ProgressionOperation>

    The list of operations to be run.

ProgressionPlayerStorage

  • projectId:  UUID?

    The project ID of the storage. Only set when returning storages for multiple projects.

  • statistics:  Array<ProgressionStatistic>

    The target channel for the progression storage.

    A list of Xbox games and what rights they have to project storage.

    Operations that should be executed automatically for all viewers every five minutes any time the game is streamed.

  • isPublished:  boolean

    If the project is published. The fiveMinuteHeartbeatOperations will only execute in test streams for unpublished projects.
